headline: US STOCKS-Wall St set to stall at open after recent run
summary: U.S. stock index futures indicated a mixed open on Tuesday after recent gains on expectations that the Federal Reserve will cut interest rates this year, as shares of Walt Disney slid following quarterly results.  Walt Disney fell 5.1% in premarket trading, as a surprise profit in its streaming entertainment division was eclipsed by a drop in its traditional TV business and weaker box office.
